      "content": "The weight you carry is real, but you are not defined by your ability to fix everything alone, and no one can truly \"see\" you if you are drowning in your own head. Many people who feel like they are failing eventually find that the pressure lifts not because they suddenly become perfect, but because they finally allow themselves to be held by others who don't expect them to carry the world. Please consider reaching out to a crisis line or a therapist who can help you navigate this crushing isolation without judgment, because you deserve support even when the future feels impossible.",
